-- Peru Declares Sugar-Industry Emergency to Permit Imports as Output Drops
-- Alex Emery
-- 2010-04-26T20:09:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/peru-declares-sugar-industry-emergency-to-permit-imports-as-output-drops.html

          
          
             Peru’s government declared a state
of emergency for 180 days in the sugar industry, enabling
companies to import sugar to offset declining production and
lower domestic prices, the Cabinet Chief’s office said today in
an e-mailed statement.  
